          facts:'A consistent pattern runs through her short tenure: Maloy grounds her rural-water and federal-lands work in genuine pre-Congress legal expertise, yet has repeatedly touted federal money — such as $45M in rural broadband — drawn from spending bills whose price tag she has publicly criticized.',
